description:
The Giovanni Clan one of the Thirteen Vampire Clans known to most vampire in the World of Darkness. Unlike other clans who have traditions that date back to Caine, they are a fairly new Bloodline. Augustus Giovanni along with others and the manipulations of Lemeth(Lamech) he diablerised(drained of his power) Ashur/Cappadocius and created his own clan in the year 1444.

ORIGIN

They were originally merchants under the name of Ioveanus during the Roman Empire. They moved to Venice during the fall of the Roman Empire and further developed their talents for Necromancy. In the year 1005 Augustus was Embraced with the blood of Cappadocius. They had wanted to bring the Giovanni family into their fold to combine their Necromantic knowledge.

Cappadocius actually wanted to understand death and God along with a plan to diablerize the Almighty. So he made a deal with Augustus who was entertaining the offers of other Vampire Clans. Cappadocius offered to make him a direct progeny of himself, which offered Augustus much more possibility of power.

In 1444 the clan was thrown into what seemed chaos but actually planned by Augustus. After diablerizing Cappadocius and his most beloved childer Japheth, they began to purge the rest of the Cappadocians. A peace with the Camarilla in 1528 brought an end to the purge with all of Cappadocians dead.

Furthering their goals to increasing their power in both financial means and in Necromancy by tearing down the Shroud, a mystic wall that separates the world of the living from a shadowland that some Necromancers can see into.

STRUCTURE

They also have a very different type of structure than other clans. Almost the entire clan is actually taken from Augustus's living descendents. They are very much like a mafia crime family.

The Clan is divided into five smaller families who then has other families some large brought into the Clan by Marriage.

Five Main Families:

The Dunsirn: Scottish bankers and cannibals

The Rossellini: near equal to the main family necromancers

The Ghiberti: Active in African Necromancers

The Pisanob: South American Necromancers

Putanesca: Sicilian thugs

Other Families by Marriage:

The St.John: Cabal of English Masons

The Rothestein: Jewish-American Kabbalists in Las Vegas

The Li Weng: Chinese Geomancers based out of San Francisco's Chinatown

The Koenig: German arms manufacturers and Death Cultists

The Hidalgo: Mexican branch(possible wiped out by the Sabbat)

The Beryn: Flemish traders with inroads to Africa

THE MASQUERADE

The Giovanni maintain even their own Masquerade from their own family. Most are unaware that they are more than a powerful Mafia Family and may be aware that the family is into some unusual things the power of the Masquerade keeps them in the dark. Most people do not want to believe in things that go bump in the night and may have even seen things but refuse to believe it. They are just like any other criminal organization and their enemies, even the ones that know usually won't reveal anything for fear of breaking the Masquerade bringing all kinds of reprisal from other Clans or forbid the Camarilla.

GHOULS

Ghouls are made by feeding a human vampire blood. This give the ghoul enhanced physical attributes. In the Giovanni family it is akin to making them a Made Man, it is a rite of passage. They practice strange rituals due to their estrangement to Catholicism. The rituals they have learned while alive may be similar to their unlife but changed to fit their now absent faith with blood replacing holy water and so on. To an to an outsider it would be very very bad. Torture and killing are very normal and their ability to bring back the dead after they kill them means they don't need to hold back when causing pain or risk killing someone before they get needed information.

GIFTS & DISIPLINES

In the World of Darkness all Vampires are descendents of Cain. Cursed for his murder of his brother. Each lineage as it grows further from Cain is weaker. Most vampires fall into one of the Thirteen Clans family lines. The Giovanni actually took over a Clan and the way they operate are developing a relatively new powers to their family. Previous to their induction the Cappadocians were learning Necromancy but nothing like what the Giovanni brought to the table. Intertwining those abilities with their Vampiric Blood gives them some unique abilities. There are some in the Clan who exibit different Traits and Powers or perhaps members of other Clans who have submitted.

POTENCE: Supernatural strength. All vampires may have some inhuman strength but this is more akin performing greater feats such as lifting cars and putting holes in concrete walls. More powerful vampires may even equal or surpass normal Lycan strength. Examples may including hitting the ground so hard as to cause tremors that break the ground locally.

DOMINATE: The ability to command, hypnotically control people, or make them forget anything. This eventually leads to possession and puppetry of individuals and may be done at great distances in the higher generations of vampires.

NECROMANCY: The Sepulchre Path is the ability to speak with the dead and even raise the dead for the more experienced and to summon and control Spirits in the stronger Kine. The Bone path can lead to controlling dead flesh, soul stealing, inserting demons into dead bodies while the Ash Path allows them to see the Negative Plain and communicate with wraiths and eventually control them. It not uncommon for them to know actual magic as well and perform Necromatic Rituals
name: Giovanni Clan

deck: A group of Asian American superheroes that came together to promote the bone marrow registry and stayed together to battle invading aliens.
description:
History

After a bone marrow donation awareness event was over a group of Asian American heroes were confronted by aliens. The aliens were invaders from the planet Seknarf Seven and came to New York City to capture humans for consumption. The initial battle with the aliens was won, but they were able to teleport the heroes along with a large number of New Yorkers to an isolated piece of land outside their home planet. It was here that Jimmy Woo decided to call their little group the Protectors.
name: Protectors

deck: Operating under the jurisdiction of Time Law, the Time Police are led by Professor Tock to ensure that no time laws are broken.
description:
Origin

Formed to police the times. Led by Professor Tock.

Creation

Written by Zac Gorman and drawn by CJ Cannon.

Major Story Arcs

When Rick and Morty use a device to merge realities (likely murdering billions of people) in order to get a let up on the stock market, the Time Police are called in to arrest the two. After some fighting, the Time Police finally arrest Rick and Morty and escort them to Time Court.
